  <string name="about">&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="0944b5"&gt;Meter Reader v1.0.2 &lt;/font&gt; &lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="0944b5"&gt;Purpose:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Graph water usage. Get notified when too much water has been used on the previous day.&lt;/br&gt;&lt;/br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="0944b5"&gt;Note:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;This app itself does &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; communicate with smart meters. It simply graphs the data and can send notifications.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="0944b5"&gt;Setup:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;In order for this app to show usage, you will need the following:&lt;/br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;hardware (an rtl-sdr compatible device, such as this &lt;a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B011HVUEME"&gt;one&lt;/a&gt;.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/bemasher/rtlamr"&gt;software&lt;/a&gt; for reading the meter (use JSON output), and a web server to host the daily log.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;li&gt;consumption log (&lt;a href="https://github.com/elliotn/MeterReaderGraph/tree/master/utils"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; you can find a script to generate/append to daily log and a cronjob to run the script daily.)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="0944b5"&gt;Usage:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;After a few readings have occurred, set the URL in the app, and graph the data.&lt;/br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You can also tell the app to automatically notify you if some threshold is reached via settings. (E.g., too much water was consumed.)&lt;/br&gt;&lt;/br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="0944b5"&gt;Release Notes:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;v1.0.2 - Added average daily line graph.&lt;/br&gt;&lt;br&gt;v1.0.1 - Bug fix for threshold alarm.&lt;/br&gt;&lt;br&gt;v1.0 - Initial release.&lt;/br&gt;&lt;/br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;font color="0944b5"&gt;Credits:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Openclipart meter &lt;a href="https://openclipart.org/detail/172388/power-meter"&gt;icon&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/br&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/PhilJay/MPAndroidChart"&gt;MPAndroidChart&lt;/a&gt; for Android graphing library.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/br&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/bemasher/rtlamr"&gt;rtlamr&lt;/a&gt; for actually reading the meter.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/br&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;</string>
